{"title_page": "Pasir Ris\u2013Punggol Group Representation Constituency", "text_new": "{{more footnotes|date=October 2013}}\n{{Infobox constituency\n|type=Group Representation\n|name=Pasir Ris\u2013Punggol\n|year=2001\n|parl_name=[[Parliament of Singapore]]\n|member=[[Teo Chee Hean]]<br />[[Ng Chee Meng]]<br />[[Teo Ser Luck]]<br />[[Janil Puthucheary]]<br />[[Sun Xueling]]<br />[[Zainal Sapari]]\n|image=Pasir Ris-Punggol Group Representation Constituency locator map.png\n|region=Northeastern [[Singapore]]\n|elects_howmany=6\n|electorate=242,067\n|local_council_label=Town Council\n|local_council=Pasir Ris\u2013Punggol\n}}\n\n'''Pasir Ris\u2013Punggol Group Representation Constituency''' ([[Traditional Chinese character|Traditional Chinese]]: \u767d\u6c99\u2013\u699c\u9d5d\u96c6\u9078\u5340;[[Simplified Chinese character|Simplified Chinese]]: \u767d\u6c99\u2013\u699c\u9e45\u96c6\u9009\u533a) is a six-member [[Group Representation Constituency]] (GRC) in the [[North-East Region, Singapore|north-eastern]] region of [[Singapore]]. The constituency consists of [[Pasir Ris]], [[Punggol]] and Compassvale in central [[Sengkang]] and small sections of [[Tampines]]. Formed during the [[2001 Singapore general election|2001 general election]] as a five-member GRC, it has been held by the [[People's Action Party]] ever since. With the growth in population of [[Punggol New Town]] and [[Sengkang New Town]], the GRC grew from a five-member GRC to a six-member GRC prior to the [[2006 Singapore general election|2006 elections]]. In 2011, Punggol East was carved out as a [[Punggol East SMC|SMC]] while the Punggol West division was formed, and in 2015, parts of Buangkok and Hougang (of the Punggol South division) were split off into [[Ang Mo Kio GRC]], while the northern portions of Punggol were formed to create the division of Punggol Coast, retaining its six seats.\n\nIts first contest happened in 2006 with the opponent being [[Singapore Democratic Alliance]]. For the [[2011 Singapore general election|2011 general election]], the incumbent [[People's Action Party]] announced that their team would be led by Teo Chee Hean, and include then-Senior Parliamentary Secretary [[Teo Ser Luck]], [[Penny Low]], as well as new candidates [[Janil Puthucheary]], [[Gan Thiam Poh]] and [[Zainal Sapari]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Ramesh|first=S|title=GE: PAP announces election line-up|url=http://www.channelnewsasia.com/stories/singaporelocalnews/view/1123709/1/.html|accessdate=21 April 2011|newspaper=Channel NewsAsia|date=19 April 2011}}</ref> In the [[2015 Singaporean general election|2015 general election]], Penny Low retired from politics and new candidates [[Ng Chee Meng]] and [[Sun Xueling]] joined the team.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Chew|first=Hui Min|url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/pap-introduces-2-new-faces-in-pasir-ris-punggol-team-ex-defence-chief-ng-chee-meng-sun|title=PAP introduces 2 new faces in Pasir Ris-Punggol team: Ex-defence chief Ng Chee Meng, Sun Xueling|date=22 August 2015|work=The Straits Times|access-date=19 February 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, the GRC is reduced to five members, with [[Punggol West Single Member Constituency|Punggol West SMC]] carved out from the current boundaries and the Sengkang Central ward becomes the founding constituency for the brand new [[Sengkang Group Representation Constituency|Sengkang GRC]], along with previous divisions of Punggol East and Sengkang South. The [[Tampines]] retail park (part of the Pasir Ris area) was also redrawn into [[Tampines GRC]].<ref>{{Cite web |last1=Sim |first1=Royston |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/politics/singapore-ge-new-electoral-boundaries-announced-14-smcs-17-grcs-in-next-election |title=Singapore GE: New electoral boundaries announced; 14 SMCs, 17 GRCs in next election |website=The Straits Times |access-date=13 March 2020 |date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/general-election-ebrc-electoral-boundaries-grc-smc-12535200|title=More electoral divisions, no 6-member GRCs in coming election: EBRC report|website=CNA|language=en|access-date=13 March 2020|date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\nCurrently, Pasir Ris\u2013Punggol GRC is led by both [[Senior Minister]] and [[Co-ordinating Minister for National Security]] [[Teo Chee Hean]] and the Secretary-General of NTUC and [[Prime Minister's Office (Singapore)|Minister in the Prime Minister's Office]] [[Ng Chee Meng]].\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n<ref>{{cite news|last=Puthucheary|first=Janil|title=Thank You Parade|url=https://www.facebook.com/photo.php?fbid=10156025743565183&set=a.10150446069490183.635248.846270182&type=1&fref=nf|accessdate=12 September 2015|newspaper=Facebook|date=12 September 2015}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable\" align=\"center\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n| '''Election ''' || '''Division ''' || '''Incumbent''' || colspan=\"2\" |'''Party'''\n|-\n![[1997 Singaporean general election|1997]] || \n* Pasir Ris Central ([[Pasir Ris Group Representation Constituency|Pasir Ris GRC]])\n* Pasir Ris Elias ([[Pasir Ris Group Representation Constituency|Pasir Ris GRC]])\n* Pasir Ris Loyang ([[Pasir Ris Group Representation Constituency|Pasir Ris GRC]])\n* Punggol East ([[Cheng San Group Representation Constituency|Cheng San GRC]])\n* Punggol Central ([[Cheng San Group Representation Constituency|Cheng San GRC]]) \n|| \n* [[Teo Chee Hean]]\n* [[Charles Chong You Fook]]\n* Ahmad bin Mohd Magad\n* Zainul Abidin Mohamed Rasheed\n* Michael Lim Chun Leng\n| bgcolor={{People's Action Party/meta/color}} | || [[People's Action Party|PAP]]\n|-\n|colspan=5 bgcolor=black |<span style=\"color:white;\">'''Formation'''</span>\n|-\n![[2001 Singaporean general election|2001]] || \n* Pasir Ris East\n* Pasir Ris West\n* Punggol North\n* Punggol South\n* Punggol Central\n|| \n* Ahmad bin Mohd Magad\n* [[Teo Chee Hean]]\n* [[Penny Low]]\n* [[Charles Chong You Fook]]\n* Michael Lim Chun Leng\n| bgcolor={{People's Action Party/meta/color}}