{"title_page": "Fu-te Ni", "text_new": "{{Infobox baseball biography\n| name       = Fu-Te Ni\n| image      = Fu-Te Ni 2010.jpg\n| image_size      = 240px\n| caption    = Ni with the [[2010 Detroit Tigers season|Detroit Tigers in 2010]]\n| team       = Fubon Guardians\n| number     = 36\n| position   = [[Relief Pitcher]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1982|11|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Pingtung County]], [[Taiwan]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| bats       = Left\n| throws     = Left\n|debutleague = CPBL\n| debutdate  = March 18\n| debutyear  = 2007\n| debutteam  = Chinatrust Whales\n| statyear   = 2007 season\n|debut2league = MLB\n| debut2date  = June 29\n| debut2year  = 2009\n| debut2team  = Detroit Tigers\n| stat2year   = 2010 season\n|statleague = MLB\n| stat1label = [[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n| stat1value = 0\u20131\n| stat2label = [[Earned run average]]\n| stat2value = 4.33\n| stat3label = [[Strikeout]]s\n| stat3value = 43\n| stat4label =\n| stat4value =\n| stat5label =\n| stat5value =\n| stat6label =\n| stat6value =\n| awards     =\n| teams      = \n*[[Chinatrust Whales]] ({{by|2007}}\u2013{{by|2008}})\n*[[Detroit Tigers]] ({{mlby|2009}}\u2013{{mlby|2010}})\n*[[Fubon Guardians|EDA Rhinos/Fubon Guardians]] ({{by|2015}}\u2013present)\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title=Fu-Te Ni\n|pic=Fu-Te Ni on November 6, 2015.jpg\n|picsize=200px\n|piccap=Ni pitching for the [[Chinese Taipei national baseball team|Chinese Taipei national team]] in [[2015 WBSC Premier12]] warm-up game\n|collapse=yes\n|c=\u502a\u798f\u5fb7\n|showflag=p\n|p=N\u00ed F\u00fad\u00e9\n|w=Ni Fu-Te\n|poj=G\u00ea Hok-tek\n|mi={{IPAc-cmn|n|i|2|-|f|u|2|d|e|2}}\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Ni (surname)|Ni]]}}\n\n'''Fu-Te Ni''' (born 14 November 1982)<ref name=sref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ni/ni-fu-te-1.html |accessdate=18 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121214155044/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ni/ni-fu-te-1.html |archivedate=14 December 2012 }}</ref> is a [[Taiwan]]ese professional [[baseball]] [[pitcher]] for the [[Fubon Guardians]] of the [[Chinese Professional Baseball League]].  Ni was a professional baseball player from Taiwan's [[Chinese Professional Baseball League]] (CPBL). After his franchise, the [[Chinatrust Whales]], disbanded on November 11, 2008, he signed a minor league contract with the [[Detroit Tigers]] in 2009.\n\nNi was called up to the [[Major League Baseball|Major Leagues]] in June 2009, becoming the sixth Taiwanese player to enter Major League Baseball. He is also the first player to transition from the CPBL to MLB. Ni made his major league debut on June 29, 2009 against the [[Oakland Athletics]].\n\n== Career ==\n===Chinatrust Whales===\nNi was drafted by the [[Chinese Professional Baseball League|CPBL]] team [[Chinatrust Whales]] in 2005. He signed with the team in early 2007 and played for the entire CPBL 2007 and 2008 seasons. In the two years Ni had a 12\u201324 record with seven holds, four saves and a 3.43 [[earned run average|ERA]] in 267\u2154 inning pitched. Ni won the [[List of CPBL strikeout champions|CPBL strikeout Champion Award]] in 2008 season with 132 [[strikeout]]s.\n\n=== Detroit Tigers ===\n[[File:Fu-Te Ni 2009.jpg|thumb|Ni with the [[2009 Detroit Tigers season|Detroit Tigers in 2009]]]]\nNi signed as a free agent with the [[Detroit Tigers]] on January 13, 2009. He was assigned to the Triple-A [[Toledo Mud Hens]] of the [[International League]]. In 24 games with the Mud Hens, Ni went 3\u20130 with a 2.60 ERA, and 32 strikeouts. Ni was called up on June 28, 2009 to replace the injured [[Nate Robertson]].<ref name=\"robertson2dl\">{{cite web | title=Tigers place Robertson on 15-day DL | website=[[MLB.com]] | date=June 28, 2009 | accessdate=June 28, 2009 | url=http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090628&content_id=5579022&vkey=news_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630123738/http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090628&content_id=5579022&vkey=news_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det | archive-date=June 30, 2009 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Tigers put LHP Nate Robertson on disabled list | newspaper=[[USA Today]] | date=June 28, 2009 | accessdate=June 28, 2009 | url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/baseball/al/2009-06-28-3106064387_x.htm}}</ref>  Ni is the sixth Taiwanese player to enter Major League Baseball, and the fourth pitcher.<ref>{{cite news | title=Local pitcher closes on major-league debut | publisher=Government Information Office, Republic of China (Taiwan) | date=June 29, 2009 | accessdate=July 5, 2009 | url=http://taiwanjournal.nat.gov.tw/ct.asp?xitem=53637&CtNode=416}} {{Dead link|date=July 2010}}</ref> He made his debut on June 29, 2009 against the [[Oakland Athletics]], allowing one run in 1.2 innings with 3 strikeouts. The first major league batter he faced was slugger [[Jason Giambi]], and Ni [[strikeout|struck him out]]. Ni pitched 36 games with the Tigers in 2009 and compiled no [[win\u2013loss record (pitching)|wins or losses]] with a 2.61 ERA and 21 strikeouts.\n\nAfter accumulating a 6.65 ERA in 2010, Ni was optioned to the back to the Mud Hens on June 30, 2010.<ref>[http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20100630&content_id=11761060&notebook_id=11761066&vkey=notebook_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det Tigers option reliever Ni to Triple-A] MLB.com June 30, 2010</ref>\n\nIn February 2011 the Tigers listed him as a non-roster invitee to spring training camp.<ref>[http://www.detnews.com/article/20110210/SPORTS0104/102100309/1129/Tigers-spring-training-roster] 2011 Tigers spring training roster</ref>\nOn March 22, he was assigned to the  Mud Hens.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tigers add six to roster, outright Ni to Triple-A|url=http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20101119&content_id=16157750&vkey=news_mlb&fext=.jsp&c_id=mlb|work=Tigers add six to roster, outright Ni to Triple-A|publisher=MLB.com|accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> He was 6\u20133 with a 3.24 ERA in 34 games (including 12 starts). Ni was released by the Tigers on August 7, 2012 after he was 2\u20132 with a 4.56 ERA in 7 games (5 starts) during the 2012 season.\n\n=== Los Angeles Dodgers ===\nAfter not playing during the 2013 season, Ni was signed by the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] to a minor league contract on December 13, 2013. However, he was released on March 31, 2014.\n\n=== Independent Baseball ===\nNi spent the 2014 season playing in the [[Atlantic League of Professional Baseball|Atlantic League]] for two different teams. He began the year with the [[Lancaster Barnstormers]] before getting traded to the [[Camden Riversharks]] for future considerations.\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Fu-Te Ni on November 6, 2015.jpg|thumb|Ni in 2015]]\nNi selected [[Chinese Taipei national baseball team]] at the [[Baseball at the 2008 Olympics|2008 Olympics]], [[2009 World Baseball Classic]], 2013 exhibition games against [[Japan national baseball team|Japan]], [[2015 WBSC Premier12]], 2016 exhibition game against Japan and [[2017 World Baseball Classic]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Major League Baseball players from Taiwan]]\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Portal bar|Biography|Baseball|Taiwan}}\n{{Commons category|Fu-Te Ni}}\n{{Baseballstats |mlb=547820 |espn=30179 |br=n/nifu01 |fangraphs=4199|brm=ni----001fut}}, or Fu-Te Ni's online [http://www.wretch.cc/album/LoveFude Album].\n\n{{s-start|header={{s-ach|aw}}}}\n{{Succession box| before = Joey Dawley| title = [[List of CPBL strikeout champions|CPBL Strikeout Champion Award]]| years = 2008  | after = [[Itsuki Shoda]]}}\n{{S-end}}\n\n{{Chinese Taipei roster 2009 World Baseball Classic}}\n{{Chinese Taipei roster 2017 World Baseball Classic}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Ni, Fu-Te}}\n[[Category:1982 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Adelaide Bite players]]\n[[Category:Baseball players at the 2008 Summer Olympics]]\n[[Category:Camden Riversharks players]]\n[[Category:Chinatrust Whales players]]\n[[Category:Detroit Tigers players]]\n[[Category:EDA Rhinos players]]\n[[Category:Fubon Guardians players]]\n[[Category:Lancaster Barnstormers players]]\n[[Category:Leones del Caracas players]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball pitchers]]\n[[Category:Major League Baseball players from Taiwan]]\n[[Category:Olympic baseball players of Taiwan]]\n[[Category:People from Pingtung County]]\n[[Category:Taiwanese expatriate baseball players in the United States]]\n[[Category:Toledo Mud Hens players]]\n[[Category:2009 World Baseball Classic players]]\n[[Category:2015 WBSC Premier12 players]]\n[[Category:2017 World Baseball Classic players]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox baseball biography\n| name       = Fu-Te Ni\n| image      = Fu-Te Ni 2010.jpg\n| image_size      = 240px\n| caption    = Ni with the [[2010 Detroit Tigers season|Detroit Tigers in 2010]]\n| team       = Fubon Guardians\n| number     = 36\n| position   = [[Relief Pitcher]]\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|df=yes|1982|11|14}}\n| birth_place = [[Pingtung County]], [[Taiwan]]\n| death_date =\n| death_place =\n| bats       = Left\n| throws     = Left\n|debutleague = CPBL\n| debutdate  = March 18\n| debutyear  = 2007\n| debutteam  = Chinatrust Whales\n| statyear   = 2007 season\n|debut2league = MLB\n| debut2date  = June 29\n| debut2year  = 2009\n| debut2team  = Detroit Tigers\n| stat2year   = 2010 season\n|statleague = MLB\n| stat1label = [[Win\u2013loss record (pitching)|Win\u2013loss record]]\n| stat1value = 0\u20131\n| stat2label = [[Earned run average]]\n| stat2value = 4.33\n| stat3label = [[Strikeout]]s\n| stat3value = 43\n| stat4label =\n| stat4value =\n| stat5label =\n| stat5value =\n| stat6label =\n| stat6value =\n| awards     =\n| teams      = \n*[[Chinatrust Whales]] ({{by|2007}}\u2013{{by|2008}})\n*[[Detroit Tigers]] ({{mlby|2009}}\u2013{{mlby|2010}})\n*[[Fubon Guardians|EDA Rhinos/Fubon Guardians]] ({{by|2015}}\u2013present)\n}}\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title=Fu-Te Ni\n|pic=Fu-Te Ni on November 6, 2015.jpg\n|picsize=200px\n|piccap=Ni pitching for the [[Chinese Taipei national baseball team|Chinese Taipei national team]] in [[2015 WBSC Premier12]] warm-up game\n|collapse=yes\n|c=\u502a\u798f\u5fb7\n|showflag=p\n|p=N\u00ed F\u00fad\u00e9\n|w=Ni Fu-Te\n|poj=G\u00ea Hok-tek\n|mi={{IPAc-cmn|n|i|2|-|f|u|2|d|e|2}}\n}}\n{{Chinese name|[[Ni (surname)|Ni]]}}\n\n'''Fu-Te Ni''' (born 14 November 1982)<ref name=sref>{{cite Sports-Reference |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ni/ni-fu-te-1.html |accessdate=18 July 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121214155044/http://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/ni/ni-fu-te-1.html |archivedate=14 December 2012 }}</ref> is a [[Taiwan]]ese professional [[baseball]] [[pitcher]] for the [[Fubon Guardians]] of the [[Chinese Professional Baseball League]].  Ni was a professional baseball player from Taiwan's [[Chinese Professional Baseball League]] (CPBL). After his franchise, the [[Chinatrust Whales]], disbanded on November 11, 2008, he signed a minor league contract with the [[Detroit Tigers]] in 2009.\n\nNi was called up to the [[Major League Baseball|Major Leagues]] in June 2009, becoming the sixth Taiwanese player to enter Major League Baseball. He is also the first player to transition from the CPBL to MLB. Ni made his major league debut on June 29, 2009 against the [[Oakland Athletics]].\n\n== Career ==\n===Chinatrust Whales===\nNi was drafted by the [[Chinese Professional Baseball League|CPBL]] team [[Chinatrust Whales]] in 2005. He signed with the team in early 2007 and played for the entire CPBL 2007 and 2008 seasons. In the two years Ni had a 12\u201324 record with seven holds, four saves and a 3.43 [[earned run average|ERA]] in 267\u2154 inning pitched. Ni won the [[List of CPBL strikeout champions|CPBL strikeout Champion Award]] in 2008 season with 132 [[strikeout]]s.\n\n=== Detroit Tigers ===\n[[File:Fu-Te Ni 2009.jpg|thumb|Ni with the [[2009 Detroit Tigers season|Detroit Tigers in 2009]]]]\nNi signed as a free agent with the [[Detroit Tigers]] on January 13, 2009. He was assigned to the Triple-A [[Toledo Mud Hens]] of the [[International League]]. In 24 games with the Mud Hens, Ni went 3\u20130 with a 2.60 ERA, and 32 strikeouts. Ni was called up on June 28, 2009 to replace the injured [[Nate Robertson]].<ref name=\"robertson2dl\">{{cite web | title=Tigers place Robertson on 15-day DL | website=[[MLB.com]] | date=June 28, 2009 | accessdate=June 28, 2009 | url=http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090628&content_id=5579022&vkey=news_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090630123738/http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20090628&content_id=5579022&vkey=news_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det | archive-date=June 30, 2009 | url-status=dead | df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title=Tigers put LHP Nate Robertson on disabled list | newspaper=[[USA Today]] | date=June 28, 2009 | accessdate=June 28, 2009 | url=https://www.usatoday.com/sports/baseball/al/2009-06-28-3106064387_x.htm}}</ref>  Ni is the sixth Taiwanese player to enter Major League Baseball,and the fourth pitcher.<ref>{{cite news | title=Local pitcher closes on major-league debut | publisher=Government Information Office, Republic of China (Taiwan) | date=June 29, 2009 | accessdate=July 5, 2009 | url=http://taiwanjournal.nat.gov.tw/ct.asp?xitem=53637&CtNode=416}} {{Dead link|date=July 2010}}</ref> He made his debut on June 29, 2009 against the [[Oakland Athletics]], allowing one run in 1.2 innings with 3 strikeouts. The first major league batter he faced was slugger [[Jason Giambi]], and Ni [[strikeout|struck him out]]. Ni pitched 36 games with the Tigers in 2009 and compiled no [[win\u2013loss record (pitching)|wins or losses]] with a 2.61 ERA and 21 strikeouts.\n\nAfter accumulating a 6.65 ERA in 2010, Ni was optioned to the back to the Mud Hens on June 30, 2010.<ref>[http://detroit.tigers.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20100630&content_id=11761060&notebook_id=11761066&vkey=notebook_det&fext=.jsp&c_id=det Tigers option reliever Ni to Triple-A] MLB.com June 30, 2010</ref>\n\nIn February 2011 the Tigers listed him as a non-roster invitee to spring training camp.<ref>[http://www.detnews.com/article/20110210/SPORTS0104/102100309/1129/Tigers-spring-training-roster] 2011 Tigers spring training roster</ref>\nOn March 22, he was assigned to the  Mud Hens.<ref>{{cite web|title=Tigers add six to roster, outright Ni to Triple-A|url=http://mlb.mlb.com/news/article.jsp?ymd=20101119&content_id=16157750&vkey=news_mlb&fext=.jsp&c_id=mlb|work=Tigers add six to roster, outright Ni to Triple-A|publisher=MLB.com|accessdate=23 April 2011}}</ref> He was 6-3 with a 3.24 ERA in 34 games (including 12 starts). Ni was released by the Tigers on August 7, 2012 after he was 2-2 with a 4.56 ERA in 7 games (5 starts) during the 2012 season.\n\n=== Los Angeles Dodgers ===\nAfter not playing during the 2013 season, Ni was signed by the [[Los Angeles Dodgers]] to a minor league contract on December 13, 2013. However, he was released on March 31, 2014.\n\n=== Independent Baseball ===\nNi spent the 2014 season playing in the [[Atlantic League of Professional Baseball|Atlantic League]] for two different teams. He began the year with the [[Lancaster Barnstormers]] before getting traded to the [[Camden Riversharks]] for future considerations.\n\n==International career==\n[[File:Fu-Te Ni on November 6, 2015.jpg|thumb|Ni in 2015]]\nNi selected [[Chinese Taipei national baseball team]] at the [[Baseball at the 2008 Olympics|2008 Olympics]], [[2009 World Baseball Classic]], 2013 exhibition games against [[Japan national baseball team|Japan]], [[2015 WBSC Premier12]], 2016 exhibition game against Japan and [[2017 World Baseball Classic]].\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Major League Baseball players from Taiwan]]\n\n=