n]]<ref name=guide/><!-- Do not change unless you have a better source than the Royal Mail --> || Possibly '''S'''utton and '''M'''orden, the two post towns that are within the SM area <ref name=\"jonathan.rawle.org\">{{cite web|url=http://jonathan.rawle.org/2006/07/03/postcodes-in-the-uk/|title=Postcodes in the UK - Jonathan Rawle's Website|website=jonathan.rawle.org|accessdate=29 April 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180429153451/http://jonathan.rawle.org/2006/07/03/postcodes-in-the-uk/|archivedate=29 April 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[SN postcode area|SN]] || [[Swindon]]||\n|-\n| [[SO postcode area|SO]] || [[Southampton]]||\n|-\n| [[SP postcode area|SP]] || [[Salisbury]] || [[Salisbury Plain|'''S'''alisbury '''P'''lain]] ||\n|-\n| [[SR postcode area|SR]] || [[Sunderland, Tyne and Wear|Sunderland]]||\n|-\n| [[SS postcode area|SS]] || [[Southend-on-Sea]]||\n|-\n| [[ST postcode area|ST]] || [[Stoke-on-Trent]]||\n|-\n| [[SW postcode area|SW]] || South West [[London]]||\n|-\n| [[SY postcode area|SY]] || [[Shrewsbury, Shropshire|Shrewsbury]]||\n|-\n| [[TA postcode area|TA]] || [[Taunton, Somerset|Taunton]]||\n|-\n| [[TD postcode area|TD]] || [[Tweeddale]]||\n|-\n| [[TF postcode area|TF]] || [[Telford]]||\n|-\n| [[TN postcode area|TN]] || [[Tunbridge Wells]]<ref name=guide/>||\n|-\n| [[TQ postcode area|TQ]] || [[Torquay]]||\n|-\n| [[TR postcode area|TR]] || [[Truro]]||\n|-\n| [[TS postcode area|TS]] || [[Teesside]]||\n|-\n| [[TW postcode area|TW]] || [[Twickenham]]||\n|-\n| [[UB postcode area|UB]] ||[[Southall]]<ref name=\"guide\" /><!-- Do not change unless you have a better source than Royal Mail -->||[[Uxbridge|'''U'''x'''b'''ridge]]\n|-\n| [[W postcode area|W]] || West [[London]]||\n|-\n| [[WA postcode area|WA]] || [[Warrington, England|Warrington]]||\n|-\n| [[WC postcode area|WC]] || Western Central [[London]]||\n|-\n| [[WD postcode area|WD]] || [[Watford]]||\n|-\n| [[WF postcode area|WF]] || [[Wakefield]]||\n|-\n| [[WN postcode area|WN]] || [[Wigan]]||\n|-\n| [[WR postcode area|WR]] || [[Worcester]]||\n|-\n| [[WS postcode area|WS]] || [[Walsall]]||\n|-\n| [[WV postcode area|WV]] || [[Wolverhampton]]||\n|-\n| [[YO postcode area|YO]] || [[York]]||\n|-\n| [[ZE postcode area|ZE]] || [[Lerwick]]<ref name=guide/><!-- Do not change unless you have a better source than the Royal Mail -->|| [[Shetland|'''Ze'''tland]]\n|}\n\n==Crown dependencies==\nThe [[Crown dependency|Crown dependencies]] (which are not part of the United Kingdom) did not introduce postcodes until later, but use a similar coding scheme. They are separate postal authorities.<ref name=guide/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Postcode area|| Postcode area name  \n|-\n| [[GY postcode area|GY]] || [[Guernsey]]\n|-\n| [[JE postcode area|JE]] || [[Jersey]]\n|-\n| [[IM postcode area|IM]] || [[Isle of Man]]\n|}\n\n==Defunct postcode areas==\n===London NE and S===\n{{further|London postal district#Abolition of NE and S divisions and retraction of E division}}\n\n===Glasgow===\nGlasgow, like London, was divided into compass districts: C, W, NW, N, E, SE, S, SW. When postcodes were introduced, these were mapped into the new ''G'' postcode: C1 became G1, W1 became G11, N1 became G21, E1 became G31, S1 became G41, SW1 became G51, and so on. As NW and SE had never been subdivided they became G20 and G40 respectively.\n\n===Norwich and Croydon===\nNorwich and Croydon were used for a postcode experiment in the late 1960s, which was replaced by the current system. The format was of the form NOR or CRO followed by two numbers and a letter, e.g. NOR 07A.\n\n==Non-geographic postcodes==\n{{further|Postcodes in the United Kingdom#Non-geographic codes}}\n\nNote that a number of non-geographic postcode sectors are also contained within geographic postcode areas.\n\n===GIR===\nGIR 0AA is a postcode created for [[Girobank]] in [[Bootle]]. It remained in use by its successors when Girobank was taken over by [[Alliance & Leicester]] and subsequently by [[Santander UK]].\n\n===BF===\nThe BF postcode area was introduced in 2012 to provide optional postcodes for [[British Forces Post Office]] addresses, for consistency with the layout of other UK addresses. It uses the national non-geographic [[post town]] \"[[BFPO]]\" and, as of 2012, the postcode district \"BF1\".\n\n===BX===\nThe non-geographic postcode area BX has been introduced for addresses which do not include a locality: this allows large organisations long-term flexibility as to where they receive their mail.  This postcode area is used by [[Lloyds Banking Group]] (BX1 1LT) and parts of the [[HM Revenue and Customs]] like VAT Central Unit (BX5 5AT) and Pay as You Earn (BX9 1AS).  Lloyds Bank also use BX4.  After splitting from Lloyds, [[TSB Bank (United Kingdom)|TSB Bank]] uses BX4 7SB, the latter part of which, when written, looks similar to \"TSB\".\n\n===XX===\nThe non-geographic postcode area XX is used by online retailers for returns by Royal Mail.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Retailer !! XX Postcodes\n|-\n| [[Amazon.co.uk]] || XX10 1DD (Scottish Distribution Centre)<ref>{{cite tweet|user=AmazonHelp|author=Amazon Help|number=790603627333292032|date=24 October 2016|title=@MarkWickson This postcode is a non-geographic code used by us for returns carried by Royal Mail to our returns center Dunfermline, SCT. ^SW}}</ref><br>XX50 1DD (ditto)<br>XX30 1FF (South West Distribution Centre)\n|-\n| [[ASOS.com]] || XX10 1AA\n|-\n| [[Boohoo.com]] || XX10 1BB \n|-\n| [[John Lewis & Partners|John Lewis]] || XX10 1EE\n|-\n| [[Very.co.uk]] || XX20 1BD\n|-\n|[[musicMagpie]]\n|XX20 1BF\n|-\n|[[Hewlett-Packard|HP]]\n|XX40 1EH\n|-\n| [[Zara (retailer)|Zara]] || XX40 1EJ\n|-\n| [[Mango]] || XX40 1EN\n|-\n| [[Monsoon Accessorize]] || XX40 1EP\n|-\n| [[Boden.co.uk]] || XX40 1EG\n|}\n\n==Overseas territories==\nCertain [[British Overseas Territories]] have postcodes:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Postcode || Location\n|-\n|AI-2640 || [[Anguilla]]<ref name=anguillian>[https://web.archive.org/web/20100514113153/http://www.festival.ai/article/view/5274 \"Anguilla Has A Postal Code, AI-2640\"], ''The Anguillian'', 12 October 2007</ref>\n|-\n|<br>ASCN 1ZZ <br>STHL 1ZZ <br>TDCU 1ZZ || [[Saint Helena, Ascension and Tristan da Cunha]]: <br>[[Ascension Island]] <br>[[Saint Helena]] <br>[[Tristan da Cunha]]<ref name=bbc_tdcu>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/4129636.stm First postcode for remote UK isle] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081224142811/http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/uk/4129636.stm |date=2008-12-24 }}. [[BBC News]]. 7 August 2005.</ref>\n|-\n|BBND 1ZZ || [[British Indian Ocean Territory]]\n|-\n|BIQQ 1ZZ || [[British Antarctic Territory]]\n|-\n|FIQQ 1ZZ || [[Falkland Islands]]\n|-\n|GX11 1AA || [[Gibraltar]]\n|-\n|PCRN 1ZZ || [[Pitcairn Islands]]\n|-\n|SIQQ 1ZZ || [[South Georgia and the South Sandwich Islands]]\n|-\n|TKCA 1ZZ || [[Turks and Caicos Islands]]<ref name=upu>[http://www.upu.int/post_code/en/countries/TCA.pdf Turks and Caicos Islands]. Bureau International UPU.</ref>\n|-\n|BFPO 57 / BF1 2AT(Akrotiri) <br> BFPO 58 / BF1 2AU (Dhekelia)||[[Akrotiri and Dhekelia]]\n|-\n|[http://www.bpo.bm/Lists/Postal%20Codes/Attachments/1/Bermuda%20Postal%20Codes%20and%20Parishes%202013.pdf List] || [[Bermuda]]\n|-\n|[http://www.caymanpost.gov.ky/portal/page/portal/poshome/posnpimages/POSTCODE%20FINDER%20COLOUR.pdf List] || [[Cayman Islands]]\n|-\n|[http://www.bvi.gov.vg/content/what-are-postcodes-addresses-british-virgin-islands List] || [[British Virgin Islands]]\n|-\n|[http://www.gov.ms/wp-content/uploads/2014/02/Postal-Code-Guide-pamphlet.pdf List] || [[Montserrat]]\n|}\n\nThese were introduced to prevent mail being sent to the wrong place, e.g., for St Helena to [[St Helens, Merseyside|St Helens]], [[Merseyside]]<ref>[ftp://ftp.royalmail.com/Downloads/public/cmwalk/doc/active/doc41000003/Courier%20Landmark%20Article%20Oct_09.pdf Landmark birthday for postcode]{{dead link|date=May 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref> and Ascension Island to [[Asunci\u00f3n]], [[Paraguay]], and many on-line companies will not accept addresses lacking a postcode.  Such mail is treated as international, not inland, so sufficient postage must be used.\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of postcode districts in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[Postcodes in the United Kingdom]]\n*[[UK Postcode Regions by Population]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Attached KML|display=title,inline|title=Postcode area boundaries<!-- These are slightly simplified to keep the file size manageable. See the individual postcode area articles for detailed postcode district boundaries. -->}}\n\n*[[Office for National Statistics]] - [http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/guide-method/geography/beginner-s-guide/postal/index.html Postal geography]\n*[[OpenStreetMap]] - [http://random.dev.openstreetmap.org/postcodes/?zoom=6&lat=54.65546&lon=-1.492&layers=000F0F0FBT Postcode map]\n*[http://strowger-net.telefoonmuseum.com/tel_info_postcodes.html Strowger net: postcodes of the UK]\n*[https://www.whichlist2.com UK Business Lists - Map of UK Postcodes]\n*[http://www.direct-marketing-lists.co.uk/postcode_map.htm Direct Marketing Lists UK postcode map ]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20080819234937/http://www.businesslistsuk.com/postcode_map.htm Business Lists UK postcode map ]\n*[http://www.gbmaps.com/postcodemaps/ukpostcodemaps.htm FREE Vector UK Postcode Maps ]\n*[[PostcodeArea]] - [http://www.postcodearea.co.uk Demographics, maps, crime rates, house prices and local information for all UK postcodes]\n*[http://bigthink.com/ideas/21163 Strange Maps - Frank Jacobs - Diagrammatic Map]\n\n{{Postal services in the United Kingdom}}\n{{Postcode areas in the United Kingdom}}\n\n[[Category:Lists of postal codes|United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Postcode areas of the United Kingdom| ]]\n[[Category:Postcodes in the United Kingdom|Areas]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom geography-related lists|Postcode areas in the United Kingdom]]\n\n[[eo:Po\u015dtkodoj en Britio]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Wikipedia list article}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=November 2019}}\nThe '''list of postcode areas in the United Kingdom''' is a tabulation of the [[postcode]] areas used by [[Royal Mail]] for the purposes of directing mail within the [[United Kingdom]]. The postcode area is the largest geographical unit used and forms the initial characters of the alphanumeric [[Postcodes in the United Kingdom|UK postcode]].<ref name=guide>{{Cite book |title=Address Management Guide |edition=5th |publisher=Royal Mail Group plc |date=March 2007 |url=http://www.royalmail.com/marketing-services/address-management-unit/address-data-products/address-management-guide |accessdate=22 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121108053647/http://www.royalmail.com/marketing-services/address-management-unit/address-data-products/address-management-guide |archivedate=8 November 2012 }}</ref> There are currently 121 geographic postcode areas in use in the UK and a further 3 often combined with these covering the Crown Dependencies of Guernsey, Jersey and Isle of Man.\n\n==Subdivision==\nEach postcode area is further divided into [[List of post towns in the United Kingdom|post town]]s and [[List of postcode districts in the United Kingdom|postcode district]]s.<ref name=guide/> There are on average 20 postcode districts to a postcode area.<ref name=guide/> The [[London postal district|London]] post town is instead divided into several postcode areas.<ref name=inner>HMSO, ''The Inner London Letter Post'', (1980)</ref>\n\n==Scope==\nThe single or pair of letters chosen for postcode areas are generally intended as a [[mnemonic]] for the places served.<ref name=guide/> Postcode areas, [[post town]]s and postcode districts do not follow political boundaries and usually serve much larger areas than the place names with which they are associated. For example, within the PA postcode area the PA1 and PA78 postcode districts are 140 miles apart; and the eight postcode areas of the [[London postal district|London post town]] cover only 40% of [[Greater London]].<ref name=inner/> The remainder of its area is covered by sections of twelve adjoining postcode areas: [[EN postcode area|EN]], [[IG postcode area|IG]], [[RM postcode area|RM]], [[DA postcode area|DA]], [[BR postcode area|BR]], [[TN postcode area|TN]], [[CR postcode area|CR]], [[SM postcode area|SM]], [[KT postcode area|KT]], [[TW postcode area|TW]], [[HA postcode area|HA]] and [[UB postcode area|UB]].<ref name=inner/>\n\n==United Kingdom postcode areas==\n{{Postcode areas imagemap|size=300px|location=right}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n!Postcode area|| Postcode area name<ref name=guide/><ref name=ons2000>{{Cite book |url=http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/social-trends-rd/the-official-yearbook-of-the-united-kingdom/the-official-yearbook-of-the-united-kingdom---2000-edition/2000-edition.pdf |format=PDF |title=The Official Yearbook of the United Kingdom |edition=2000 |author=[[Office for National Statistics]] |publisher=[[The Stationery Office]] |location=London |year=1999 |isbn=0-11-621098-2 |at=\"UK Postal Areas\", map opposite p. 5 |accessdate=22 October 2012 |url-status=live |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121030121704/http://www.ons.gov.uk/ons/rel/social-trends-rd/the-official-yearbook-of-the-united-kingdom/the-official-yearbook-of-the-united-kingdom---2000-edition/2000-edition.pdf |archivedate=30 October 2012 }}</ref> || Code formation\n|-\n| [[AB postcode area|AB]] || [[Aberdeen]]||\n|-\n| [[AL postcode area|AL]] || [[St Albans]]||\n|-\n| [[B postcode area|B]] || [[Birmingham]]|| \n|-\n| [[BA postcode area|BA]] || [[Bath, Somerset|Bath]]||\n|-\n| [[BB postcode area|BB]] || [[Blackburn]]||\n|-\n| [[BD postcode area|BD]] || [[Bradford]]||\n|-\n| [[BH postcode area|BH]] || [[Bournemouth]]||\n|-\n| [[BL postcode area|BL]] || [[Bolton]]||\n|-\n| [[BN postcode area|BN]] || [[Brighton]]||\n|-\n| [[BR postcode area|BR]] || [[Bromley]]||\n|-\n| [